                     A. 54. p. 1.
                  that the Youth thereof be Educated, not only in good Litterature, but in sound Doctrine;

IT is Ordered, Decreed, and by this Court Declared; That no man shall be adjudged for the meer forbearance of any Debt, above eight pound in the hundred, for one year, and not above the Rate proportionably for all sums whatsoever, (Bills of Exchange excepted) neither shall this be a colour or countenance to allow any Usury amongst us contrary to the Law of God. [1641, 4 
